{
  "slug": "lookup-two-criteria",
  "title": "How to look up a value with two criteria (multi-condition lookup)",
  "task": "Return a value that matches on two columns at once, e.g. the amount for Region = North AND Quarter = Q2.",
  "keywords": [
    "xlookup multiple criteria",
    "lookup two conditions",
    "index match two criteria",
    "vlookup multiple columns"
  ],
  "solutions": {
    "excel": {
      "formula": "=XLOOKUP(\"North|Q2\",A2:A6&\"|\"&B2:B6,C2:C6)",
      "note": "Excel 365; concatenate the keys."
    },
    "google_sheets": {
      "formula": "=XLOOKUP(\"North|Q2\",A2:A6&\"|\"&B2:B6,C2:C6)",
      "note": "Native XLOOKUP."
    },
    "libreoffice": {
      "formula": "=XLOOKUP(\"North|Q2\",A2:A6&\"|\"&B2:B6,C2:C6)",
      "note": "LibreOffice 25.8 (XLOOKUP added 24.8)."
    }
  },
  "verify": {
    "setup_cells": {
      "A2": "North",
      "B2": "Q1",
      "C2": 100,
      "A3": "North",
      "B3": "Q2",
      "C3": 250,
      "A4": "South",
      "B4": "Q2",
      "C4": 300,
      "A5": "South",
      "B5": "Q1",
      "C5": 150,
      "A6": "North",
      "B6": "Q3",
      "C6": 400
    },
    "formula": "=XLOOKUP(\"North|Q2\",A2:A6&\"|\"&B2:B6,C2:C6)",
    "expected": 250
  },
  "explanation": "Concatenate the two key columns (A&\"|\"&B) into a single combined key, then XLOOKUP that combined key. 'North|Q2' matches row 3, returning 250. The pipe separator avoids accidental collisions between key parts."
}